Acknowledgments
---------------
This work builds upon the PairG method and utilises the Kokkos/KokkosKernels
framework for parallel computing, as well as the gum library for sequence graph
utilities, and sdsl-lite bit manipulation utilities (include/diverg/bits.hpp) by
Simon Gog.

For citation purposes, please refer to:

Ali Ghaffaari, Alexander Schönhuth, and Tobias Marschall.
"DiVerG: Scalable Distance Index for Validation of Paired-End Alignments in Sequence Graphs".
In 25th International Conference on Algorithms for Bioinformatics (WABI 2025).
Leibniz International Proceedings in Informatics (LIPIcs), Volume 344, pp. 10:1-10:24,
https://doi.org/10.4230/LIPIcs.WABI.2025.10

